<kml>
<relation-doc name=instrument>


<from name=Event>
<to name=Entity>

<description> 
  the entity that is used (by the agent if there is one) to perform an event.  
</description>

<examplesentencelist>

  <examplesentence>
    <text>John <ex-from>swatted</ex-from> the fly with <ex-to>a newspaper</ex-to>.</text>
  </examplesentence>

  <examplesentence>
    <text>Sally <ex-from>read</ex-from> the newspaper with <ex-to>a magnifying glass</ex-to>.</text>
  </examplesentence>

  <examplesentence>
    <text><ex-to>The baseball</ex-to> <ex-from>broke</ex-from> the windshield.</text>
  </examplesentence>

</examplesentencelist>

<neighborlist>
 <neighbor name=agent>
    An agent is active, while an instrument is passive, being used by the
    agent (if there is one).  An agent is typically considered sentient, 
    if only metaphorically, while an instrument is not.
 </neighbor>
</neighborlist>

</kml>
